Author: ComputerGenie#2331
Content:
it doesn't "break" anything; in simplest terms, it just makes a more "complex" computation that requires more RAM and power to solve
with 200 and 9 as values, a 1080TI uses 50 MB of RAM and can do ~740 Sol/s
with 144 and 5 as values, a 1080TI uses 2.5 GB of RAM and can do ~58 Sol/s
